<bug>
    <id>185220</id>
    <title>File|Page Setup|Margin &amp; Header/Footer never holds settings always returns to default</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Win98; en-US; rv:1.3a) Gecko/20021212 Phoenix/0.5
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Win98; en-US; rv:1.3a) Gecko/20021212 Phoenix/0.5</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">File|Page Setup|Margin &amp; Header/Footer never holds settings always returns to
default
Title, blank, url
Page # of #, blank, date &amp; time
no matter how you reset the above defaults - or how often - they always return
to the defaults.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">This has been a problem since the early Netscape and as far as
I know has never been changed.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">Can't something be done about it?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Change the defaults</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 Exit program</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">3 Reenter program - defaults are back</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Actual Results:  
As predicted</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
Want my default settings to remain.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">Shouldn't have to reset every time we want
to print a page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.3">Current default almost always results in an extra line on HP
printers.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
